Installation Instructions for ldsped
====================================


To build it you type:
        ./configure
        make
        make install

By default, it will install the files in /usr.  To change this
so that binaries go in /usr and the conf files go in /etc :
	./configure --prefix=/usr --sysconfdir=/etc --localstatedir=/var
	make
	make install


For debian and the like (i.e. Ubuntu) run
	./configure --prefix=/usr --sysconfdir=/etc --localstatedir=/var --mandir=/usr/share/man

If not, neccesary files will not be found.


To install the example configuration file type
	make installconf


To install ldsped and create a working configuration file
	./install-ldsped



  - Lieven <on7lds@amsat.org>
